   <description id="d1e249" translate="no" xml:lang="en">
      <title translate="yes">bolted assembly with welded nut: description</title>
      <descbody translate="no">
         <descsection translate="no">
            <figure id="00-04-03-108-repair-40-01-34-02-02-21-1-1-3" translate="no">
               <image dimension="F2 (85x85) #" href="../MergedPictures/ILL-000016791.PNG" style="width: 85.0mm; height: 85.0mm;" translate="no"/><illusnum>RDE-000485541-04-03-108-repair-40-01-34-02-02-21-1-1-3-000016791</illusnum>
            </figure>
            <para translate="yes">Insert the helical thread insert on to the adapted pin by placing the driving plate pin in the neck provided.</para>
            <para translate="yes">Turn the pin in the drilling hole.</para>
         </descsection>
         <descsection translate="no">
            <figure id="00-04-03-112-repair-40-01-34-02-02-21-1-1-4" translate="no">
               <image dimension="F2 (85x85) #" href="../MergedPictures/ILL-000016941.PNG" style="width: 85.0mm; height: 85.0mm;" translate="no"/><illusnum>RDE-000485541-04-03-112-repair-40-01-34-02-02-21-1-1-4-000016941</illusnum>
            </figure>
            <noteR translate="no" type="note">
               <para translate="yes">Note:</para>
               <para translate="yes">For perfect insertion of the thread insert, locate the last thread at<technicalvalue translate="no"> <value translate="yes">0.25</value> </technicalvalue>pitch below the surface of the part.</para>
            </noteR>
            <para translate="yes">Break the driving plate pin using a jet.</para>
         </descsection>
      </descbody>
   </description>
